-- China to work on financial reforms -premier
-- By Koh Gui Qing
-- Fri Sep 26, 2014 08:14AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, Sept 26 (Reuters) - China will work harder on its financial reforms by allowing more companies to enter the industry and ensuring fair competition, Premier Li Keqiang said on Friday.

China plans to build an insurance system for all bank deposits to protect savers' interests, Li reiterated in comments  published on the government's website.